overview: The user initiated a planning phase by providing a Statement of Work
  (SOW) for a "Sleep Questionnaire Application." Their primary goal was to
  assess the current codebase and identify outstanding tasks, specifically
  focusing on database implementation, a client dashboard for data access, and
  any necessary authentication middleware. The assistant performed a thorough
  review of the existing files, including Prisma schema, API routes, and
  component structures. The analysis revealed that while basic questionnaire
  types and PDF generation were present, key SOW requirements were missing.
  These include a dedicated database for storing questionnaire responses, a
  mechanism for CSV data retrieval, a client dashboard for data access, and an
  authentication system to secure the dashboard. The user is open to the
  simplest database solution, even if it's not their usual NeonDB.
